      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### What to check when throughput is zero\n\n| Area | Command / place |\n|------|-----------------|\n| **Connector task** | `curl -s http://localhost:8083/connectors/oracle-xstream-rac-connector/status` — `RUNNING`, task `RUNNING` |\n| **Connector logs** | `docker logs connect --tail 200` — look for Oracle/XStream errors, **snapshot** vs **streaming** |\n| **Oracle (MTX)** | SYSDBA: `sqlplus @oracle-database/diagnose-mtx-cdc.sql` — supplemental log, `DBA_XSTREAM_RULES`, capture `ENABLED` |\n| **table.include.list** | Must include `ORDERMGMT.MTX.*` (same PDB/service as HammerDB) |\n| **Kafka topics** | `kafka-topics --list \\| grep racdb` — topics must exist |\n| **JMX / Grafana** | Debezium panels need `debezium.confluent.oracle:*` in Connect JMX (`monitoring/jmx/kafka-connect.yml`); **restart Connect** after edits |\n\n**Note:** Small periodic spikes are often **connector heartbeat** (`heartbeat.interval.ms`), not DML. Compare MTX topic lines vs `__cflt-oracle-heartbeat` on the dashboard."
      },
      "title": "Operational checklist",
      "type": "text"
    },
